This is a bug that is currently present in Angular. You cannot use `ngStyle` or `style` to set `!important`. Here&#39;s a [link to the open bug report][1].

As a workaround until it&#39;s fixed, you can use `ngClass` instead. This is of course if you actually really need `!important` there in the first place.

```js
[ngClass]=&quot;booleanVar ? &#39;height-1&#39;: &#39;height-2&#39;&quot;
```

Then in your css
```css
.height-1 {
    height: 11px !important;
}

.height-2 {
    height: 7px !important;
}
```

  [1]: https://github.com/angular/angular/issues/12009

